metadata.name: 00: Orsae Majoris Anubis Orchid
metadata.description:
Orsae Majoris, located approximately 46 light-years from Earth in the constellation of Ursa Major is the home of the aquatic Anubis Orchid. 

The plant is fully submerged throughout its lifespan cycle absorbing nutrients and minerals.

Every 5 earth years, the Anubis Orchid blooms. 
The flowers emerge above the level of water radiating heat in magnificent colors to attract pollinated insects.
